        <h2>The Short Answer</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Anabolic resistance means aging muscle becomes less responsive to protein — the same dose triggers less muscle-building activity.</li>
          <li>The specific mechanism: the mTOR pathway requires more leucine per meal to fire after 40 — approximately 3.5–4g versus 2–2.5g for younger adults.</li>
          <li>This is why men over 40 need 30–40g of protein per meal, not just more protein overall.</li>
          <li>It's also why the RDA of 0.8g/kg per day is insufficient for older men trying to maintain muscle.</li>
          <li>Anabolic resistance is the mechanism. Sarcopenia — progressive muscle loss — is what happens when it goes unaddressed.</li>
        </ul>
